Describe a time when you came close to a wild animal
- where you were
- what the animals were doing
- who you were with
- what your reaction was

I'd like to talk about a memorable experience when I came close to a wild animal, which was when I saw and even rode an elephant in Boun Ma Thuot about 15 years ago.
At that time, I was still a primary school student, and it was during my summer vacation. My mother decided to take me on a short trip to Boun Ma Thuot, a city in Vietnam that is well known for its coffee plantations and elephant culture. During our visit, we explored several tourist attractions, and at one of them, I saw an elephant up close for the very first time.
I was honestly amazed by its size. It was enormous - much larger than I had imagined - with thick grey skin, a long trunk, and a pair of slightly yellowish tusks. The elephant was calmly walking around and carrying tourists on its back.
Interestingly, there was a service that allowed visitors to ride the elephant. As a curious child, I didn't hestitate to try it. At first, I felt quite nervous because I was sitting several meters above the ground, which was a bit intimidating. However, after a short while, I began to relax and even enjoy the experience.
At that time, I was completely unaware that element riding can be harmful to the animal, so I found it exciting. However, looking back now, I feel somewhat guilty for taking part in it. This experience has made me more aware of animal welfare, and since then, I've chosen to avoid any activities that exploit animals for entertainment.
Overall, it was an unforgettable experience - not only because it was my first close encounter with such a magnificent animal, but also because it changed the way I think about how animals should be treated.
